      "site_admin": false
    },
    "body": "<!-- markdownlint-disable -->\n\n## Purpose\n\nReduce k tensor concatenation latency, from **3.16ms to 1.61ms** for batch size 32768 (i.e., `k.shape=torch.Size([32768, 128, 192]), k_nope.shape=torch.Size([32768, 128, 128]), k_pe.shape=torch.Size([32768, 1, 64])`.\n\n<img width=\"2565\" height=\"1415\" alt=\"image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/6398017c-e2af-4aa8-ae54-a51b9d6f82d8\" />\n\n## Test Plan\n\n* verified perf improvement with trace\n* verified accuracy\n* microbenchmark: `python benchmarks/kernels/benchmark_mla_k_concat.py`\n\n## Test Result\n\nlocal-completions (model=nvidia/DeepSeek-R1-0528-FP4,base_url=http://127.0.0.1:8000/v1/completions,num_concurrent=32), gen_kwargs: (None), limit: 100.0, num_fewshot: None, batch_size: 1\n|Tasks|Version|     Filter     |n-shot|  Metric   |   |Value|   |Stderr|\n|-----|------:|----------------|-----:|-----------|---|----:|---|-----:|\n|gsm8k|      3|flexible-extract|     5|exact_match|↑  | 0.96|±  |0.0197|\n|     |       |strict-match    |     5|exact_match|↑  | 0.96|±  |0.0197|\n\n```\n================================================================================\nBenchmark: torch.cat vs direct copy for MLA k_nope/k_pe concatenation\n================================================================================\nTensor shapes: k_nope=[B, 128, 128], k_pe=[B, 1, 64]\ndtype: float8_e4m3fn\n\n  Batch Size |   cat (ms) |  direct (ms) |  Speedup |  Reduction\n----------------------------------------------------------------------\n          32 |      0.010 |        0.027 |    0.38x |    -160.6%\n          64 |      0.010 |        0.028 |    0.37x |    -169.9%\n         128 |      0.015 |        0.027 |    0.53x |     -87.0%\n         256 |      0.027 |        0.027 |    0.98x |      -1.9%\n         512 |      0.049 |        0.027 |    1.82x |      45.0%\n        1024 |      0.094 |        0.044 |    2.13x |      53.1%\n        2048 |      0.185 |        0.086 |    2.14x |      53.2%\n        4096 |      0.401 |        0.205 |    1.95x |      48.8%\n        8192 |      0.797 |        0.405 |    1.97x |      49.1%\n       16384 |      1.583 |        0.801 |    1.97x |      49.4%\n       32768 |      3.159 |        1.593 |    1.98x |      49.6%\n       65536 |      6.308 |        3.176 |    1.99x |      49.7%\n================================================================================\n\nSpeedup summary:\n  Min:  0.37x\n  Max:  2.14x\n  Mean: 1.52x\n\nConclusion:\n  - Direct copy becomes beneficial at batch size >= 512\n  - For batch sizes >= 512: avg speedup = 1.99x\n  - MLA prefill typically uses large batches, so optimization is effective\n```\n\n---\n<details>\n<summary> Essential Elements of an Effective PR Description Checklist </summary>\n\n- [ ] The purpose of the PR, such as \"Fix some issue (link existing issues this PR will resolve)\".\n- [ ] The test plan, such as providing test command.\n- [ ] The test results, such as pasting the results comparison before and after, or e2e results\n- [ ] (Optional) The necessary documentation update, such as updating `supported_models.md` and `examples` for a new model.\n- [ ] (Optional) Release notes update. If your change is user facing, please update the release notes draft in the [Google Doc](https://docs.google.com/document/d/1YyVqrgX4gHTtrstbq8oWUImOyPCKSGnJ7xtTpmXzlRs/edit?tab=t.0).\n</details>\n\n",
